# Privacy Policy

Effective date: May 28, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how LawnCore ("the App") handles information. The App is developed and provided by Vladyslav Asieiev ("we", "us", or "our").

By using the App, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

## 1. Information We Do Not Collect

We do not collect, store, sell, rent, or share your personal data through the App.

The App does not require an account and does not send your app data to our servers.

## 2. Local Data Storage

Any information you enter, create, calculate, or save in the App is stored locally on your device.

We do not have access to this locally stored data. We do not view it, process it, transfer it, or use it to identify you.

You are responsible for managing and backing up your local data. If you delete the App, reset your device, or remove app data, your locally stored information may be permanently lost.

## 3. Support Communications

If you contact us by email, we may receive your email address and any information you choose to include in your message.

We use this information only to respond to your request, provide support, or address issues you report. We do not use support emails for advertising or sell them to third parties.

## 4. App Store and Platform Data

If you download the App through the Apple App Store or another app marketplace, that platform may process certain information according to its own privacy policy and terms.

We do not control how Apple or other platforms process data related to downloads, purchases, refunds, device settings, crash reports, or app marketplace analytics.

## 5. Analytics, Tracking, and Advertising

The App does not use third-party advertising trackers.

The App does not track you across other apps or websites.

The App does not use your data for targeted advertising.

## 6. Health, Lawn, Gardening, and Property-Related Information

The App may allow you to enter or generate information related to lawn care, gardening, soil, watering, fertilization, treatments, schedules, or similar topics.

This information remains stored locally on your device unless you choose to share it outside the App.

## 7. Children’s Privacy

The App is not intended to knowingly collect personal information from children. Since we do not collect personal data through the App, we do not knowingly collect data from children.

If you believe a child has contacted us directly and provided personal information by email, please contact us and we will delete that information where appropriate.

## 8. Data Security

Because the App stores data locally on your device, the security of that data depends on your device settings, operating system, backups, and access controls.

We recommend using device-level protections such as a passcode, Face ID, Touch ID, and secure backups.

## 9. Your Choices

You can delete locally stored app data by deleting the App from your device, subject to how your operating system handles app storage and backups.

You can contact us to request deletion of support emails or other information you voluntarily sent to us.

## 10. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make changes, we will update the effective date above.

Your continued use of the App after the updated Privacy Policy becomes available means you accept the updated policy.

